			<ns0:name>col...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/101359714341338829292/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">GL_RG_EXT format support would be nice (http://www.khronos.org/registry/gles/extensions/EXT/EXT_texture_rg.txt)

Today, NaCl currently supports OES_texture_float, and OES_texture_half_float, which are 4 channel (RGBA) floating point formats.

GL_RG_EXT is a two channel floating point texture format for the GPU. Which will be very helpful in reducing memory footprint on the GPU for shadow mapping (a visual technique used in NaCl games). 

Currently, developers who want to use specific forms of shadow mapping only need one, or two channels in a floating point texture, meaning that the 4 channel textures have 2-3 extra channels in overhead and memory footprint.
